Job Title:     Security Administrator
Job Location:  PA: Broomall
Pay Rate:      Open
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    0000-00-00

Company Name:  Worlco Computer Resources Inc.
Contact:       Recruiter
Phone:         856-555-1212
Fax:           856-665-8142

Description:   The Security Administrator works under the general supervision of the Systems Administration Manager.  In working with the Systems Administration Manager, the Security Administrator is responsible for the overall security compliance from both a business and technical perspective, and leads the integration of Lawson users per the defined IT Enterprise Operating Model.

PRINCIPLE ACCOUNTABILITIES
- Responsible for management and support of Security and User Accounts within the ERP environment including security at the program, file, data, and field levels.
- Responsible for security monitoring and control of the environment and user access rights.
- Maintain documentation for all user access and develop means for providing on a timely basis as requested.
- Implement and update all security and user management support processes and procedures in accordance with audit requirements.
- Monitor and manage heat tickets (support requests) logged to the security administration team, with resolution documented correctly and adequately once resolved.
- Assess all problems and potential security issues and escalate to management.
- Assist the IT team in the delivery of information security governance, risk assessments and projects, as required.
- Work with System Administration team to implement automated monitoring policies and rules in line with security policies and standards.
- Identify security alerts and potential security issues and investigate, escalate and resolve in accordance with risk and priority.
- Refine and implement monitoring and control security policies and rules.
- Generate and review regular and ad-hoc reports and investigate, escalate and resolve identified issues.
- Regular review of user access rights on key IT environments and security systems.
- Regular validation of users and corresponding access rights.
- Evaluate new applications to ensure that they comply with the security policies and security administration requirements as required.
- Perform testing of security administration aspects of new releases and enhancements.
- Development, implementation and maintenance of monitoring and control security policies, rules and management procedures for the environment.
- Identifies, encourages and documents departmental process and procedural changes.

EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILL REQUIREMENTS
Education
- An Undergraduate Degree in Computer Science or Information Systems, or relevant work experience.
Experience
- A minimum two years security administration experience.
- Knowledge of IT applications related to healthcare and Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP).
- Previous experience with Lawson ERP Software implementation and support preferred.
- Previous experience in a UNIX environment preferred.
Skills
- Experience with security analysis, design and implementation.
- Experience documenting security and user access requirements.
- Experience in system test design, script development, test execution and documentation.
- Polished interpersonal skills to communicate tactfully, effectively and with discretion within all levels of management.

